Pop Music is basically a genre of music that has rhythmic elements, melodies and hooks. This term was first used in the year 1926. It is considered as a lighter alternative to rock and roll. The origin of pop music can be traced back to 1679 with the composition of the first opera by Alessandro Scarlatti. Or it could even be traced to earlier times when Francesco Provenzale termed the musical language as light, catchy and lively.
